# Walkthrough: AUTO Mode Pipeline Testing Setup

## Summary
Enabled and stabilized the full automated production loop testing environment for the robotic arm. This included bypassing incomplete hardware components (scale), exposing test simulation triggers directly on the lock screen, and fixing process cleanup scripts for a stable startup.

## Changes Made

### 1. Scale Simulation Bypass `[robot_logic_node.cpp]`
Hardware for the scale is currently absent. To prevent a 30-second timeout queue error causing an `ERROR_SCALE_TIMEOUT` system halt:
- Added `simulate_scale_` and `force_pass_` flags.
- Defaulted constructor values to enable these bypasses.
- Updated [stateProcessingScale()](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/robot_control_main/src/robot_logic_node.cpp#1928-1992) to immediately push a `true` (PASS) value to the `stored_scale_result_` atom and jump to `PLACE_TO_OUTPUT`.

### 2. Auto-Mode Safety & Test Triggers `[CartridgePage.qml]`
The user needed a way to publish test signals while the robot UI is locked in Auto Mode:
- Refactored the `manualEnabled` false overlay into an aesthetic `AUTO MODE OVERLAY`.
- Blocked clicks behind the overlay to "lock" manual buttons as requested.
- Added two high-visibility action buttons (`PICK INPUT` and `PICK CHAMBER`) directly on the overlay.
- Removed hardcoded state-machine forces (`goto_state`) from the simulation triggers so they publish strictly the boolean triggers (`/revpi/feed_chamber` and `/fill_machine/fill_done`).

### 3. Cleanup Stability `[start_all.sh]`
[start_all.sh](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/unified_control_gui/scripts/start_all.sh) suffered from duplicate PID exit failures and orphaned background processes on terminal detach:
- **Auto-Cleanup**: Now automatically identifies and `pkill`s zombie ROS nodes instead of failing out.
- **Signal Traps**: Added `HUP` and `QUIT` to the trap block, ensuring that terminal closure instantly signals a graceful shutdown sequence to all [start_all.sh](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/unified_control_gui/scripts/start_all.sh) children.
